<li>
<p class="">Strengthens hair follicles</p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="">Combats <a href="https://science.sciencemag.org/content/351/6273/aad4395" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">hair thinning </a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="">May stimulate thicker hair growth</p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="">Helps decrease hair brittleness</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><span>NAILS</span></h3>
<p class="">Our nails also <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7142618" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">undergo changes</a> as <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15726300" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">we age</a>, which<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3038811/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> include</a> brittleness, possible discoloration, and weaker, thinner nails. One of the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5383514/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">most vital</a> amino acids for <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2090123210000573" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">nail growth</a>, arginine, is <a href="https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2017/ra/c7ra02842c" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">found in collagen</a>. <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/28786550" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Studies</a> show that collagen helps increase nail growth, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16205932" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">reduce the brittleness</a> of nails, and decrease the frequency of nails breaking. So, taking collagen might just give you long, strong, healthy nails.</p>
